08/10/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- New figures published on Sunday (October 7th) suggest an estimated 1.02 million displaced people and refugees have returned to BiH since the Dayton Peace Accord was signed in December 1995. 
According to data from the Federation of BiH's (FBiH) Ministry of Refugees and Displaced Persons, 740,878 people returned to FBiH; 258,029 to Republika Srpska; and 21,382 to Brcko District. 
(Nezavisne Novine - 08/10/07; RTRS, NTV Hayat, PBS, Fena - 07/10/07)
